ess\n```\n\nsimple interface for {mod}`subprocess`\n\nshell is not supported (shell=False)\n\n:::{warning}\nunicode is supported only for string list command (Python2.x)\n(check {mod}`shlex` for more information)\n:::\n\n```\nparam cmd\n\nstring ('ls -l') or list of strings (['ls','-l'])\n\nparam cwd\n\nworking directory\n\nparam use_temp_files\n\nuse temp files (True) or pipes (False) for stdout and stderr,\npipes can cause deadlock in some cases (see unit tests)\n\nparam env\n\nIf env is not None, it must be a mapping that defines the environment\nvariables for the new process; these are used instead of inheriting the current\nprocess' environment, which is the default behavior.\n(check   for more information)\n```\n"]}], "exports": [{"name": "easyprocess.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "easyprocess.about.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "easyprocess.Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": null}}, {"name": "easyprocess.List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": null}}, {"name": "easyprocess.Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": null}}, {"name": "easyprocess.split_command", "xref": {"fqname": "easyprocess.unicodeutil.split_command", "project": null}}, {"name": "easyprocess.unidecode", "xref": {"fqname": "easyprocess.unicodeutil.unidecode", "project": null}}, {"name": "easyprocess.Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": null}}]}]}